              <div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Would you trust Catelyn to be smart and keep a secret?</div><br />Well to be honest, Martin's presentation of Catelyn at the beginning of book 1 is of a pretty sane woman who is smart, respectable, thoughful, honorable, and all sorts of other positive superlatives, and the only thing that gets under her skin is Jon himself. So yeah, you would think so. In fact, she might not hate Jon viscerally if he said something like, &quot;I didn't cheat on you.&quot;<br /><br />Then you read further and see how Martin changes the characters drastically over time. I wouldn't trust anyone in his world with any secret more important than, &quot;I really have to fart,&quot; in a public place.<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Yet he was still branded Kingslayer and had his honor questioned since then.</div><br />I think his still wearing the white had something to do with that...

              

              
              
            </div>
