          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              I suppose I should add that I took some medieval European history in college, and I can see that the author seems keen to point out that many of the &quot;winners&quot; in our own history were the scoundrels. This idea has merit, but it doesn't mean it will add up to enjoyable fiction. Bernard Cornwell wrote a bleak and painful Arthur story in his &quot;Winter King&quot; trilogy, but he did an admirable job (at least in hindsight) of putting good characters through grisly and painful situations without turning me off as the reader.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
